# Tom Plumb Landing Page - Environment Variables
# Copy this file to .env and fill in your actual values

# Server Configuration
PORT=3000
NODE_ENV=production

# Resend Configuration
# Get your API key from: https://resend.com/api-keys
RESEND_API_KEY=re_your_resend_api_key_here

# Email Addresses
# Business email - where lead notifications will be sent
BUSINESS_EMAIL=leads@tomplumbs.com

# From email - must be from a verified domain in Resend
# Format: noreply@yourdomain.com (or onboarding@resend.dev for testing)
NOTIFICATION_FROM_EMAIL=noreply@tomplumbs.com

# =============================================================================
# Railway Deployment Instructions:
# =============================================================================
#
# 1. Create a Railway account at https://railway.app
#
# 2. Install Railway CLI (optional):
#    npm install -g @railway/cli
#
# 3. Connect your GitHub repository to Railway:
#    - Go to Railway dashboard
#    - Click "New Project"
#    - Select "Deploy from GitHub repo"
#    - Choose your repository
#
# 4. Add Environment Variables in Railway:
#    - Go to your project in Railway
#    - Click on your service
#    - Go to "Variables" tab
#    - Add all the variables from this file with your actual values
#
# 5. Deploy:
#    - Railway will automatically deploy on git push
#    - Or click "Deploy" in Railway dashboard
#
# 6. Set up Resend:
#    - Create a Resend account at https://resend.com
#    - Add and verify your domain (or use onboarding@resend.dev for testing)
#    - Create an API key
#    - Add the API key to Railway environment variables
#
# 7. Custom Domain (optional):
#    - Go to "Settings" in Railway
#    - Click "Generate Domain" for a Railway subdomain
#    - Or add your custom domain in "Custom Domains"
#
# =============================================================================
# Local Development:
# =============================================================================
#
# 1. Copy this file:
#    cp .env.example .env
#
# 2. Fill in your values in .env
#    - For testing, you can use: onboarding@resend.dev as NOTIFICATION_FROM_EMAIL
#
# 3. Install dependencies:
#    npm install
#
# 4. Run development server:
#    npm run dev
#
# 5. Open http://localhost:3000
#
# =============================================================================
# Resend Quick Start:
# =============================================================================
#
# 1. Sign up at https://resend.com (free tier: 100 emails/day)
#
# 2. For Testing (No Domain Required):
#    - Use onboarding@resend.dev as your NOTIFICATION_FROM_EMAIL
#    - This works immediately, no verification needed
#
# 3. For Production (Your Domain):
#    - Add your domain in Resend dashboard
#    - Add DNS records to verify domain ownership
#    - Once verified, use your@domain.com emails
#
# 4. Create API Key:
#    - Go to API Keys in Resend dashboard
#    - Click "Create API Key"
#    - Copy the key (starts with "re_")
#    - Add to .env as RESEND_API_KEY
#
# =============================================================================
